      "Wellhead temporarily moved to clear deck space",
      "Injured party hoisted to platform helideck via lift boat crane",
      "Medevac helicopter evacuation to onshore hospital"
    ],
    "summary": "On 21 September 2023 at approximately 0130 hours, a night shift supervisor sustained a compound fracture with exposed bone to his lower left shin when an unsecured 8000-pound wellhead rolled onto his leg while he was seated on it during well abandonment operations on the Lift Boat Man-O-War at Eugene Island Block 158JB. The wellhead had been laid on its side on the deck in an unstable position without securing measures. The injured party was evacuated by medevac helicopter after approximately 4 hours of onsite treatment.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Keep a scrap basket onboard to contain and secure loads once on the lift boat's deck"
    ],
